TO_DO: Seems like vagrant is a good idea to streamline this...
Host preparation:
/etc/default/docker must contain:
DOCKER_OPTS="--ipv6=false --dns 8.8.8.8 --dns 8.8.4.4 -H tcp://0.0.0.0:4243 -H unix:///var/run/docker.sock"
groupadd -g 1000 jenkins
useradd -m -g 1000 -u 1000 -d /home/jenkins jenkins
mkdir -p /srv/jenkins/cmake-dependency-metadata
mkdir /srv/jenkins/dependency-information/
chown -R jenkins.jenkins /srv/jenkins
ssh-keygen (normal)
ssh-keygen /home/jenkins/.ssh/jenkins_install (no passphrase) copy this key into master jinstaller authorized_keys
Add jenkins to docker group:
sudo gpasswd -a jenkins docker
sudo systemctl restart docker (service docker restart pre systemd systems)
newgrp jenkins
On Jenkins:
Slaves images are auto generated by running create_ubuntu_slave_{host} on Jenkins.
Add new item Freestyle and copy existing create_{os}_slave_{hostname} to a new job with respective name.
docker run -v /srv/jenkins:/srv/jenkins -v /home/jenkins/.ssh:/home/jenkins/.ssh sgclarkkde/kde-slave-ubuntu
Add new docker cloud 




